Sentencas: A simple strategy has been exploited to synergistically improve the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-delta (LNF) cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) via in-situ infiltration of a Ba0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (BSC) precursor on the LNF backbone.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction

Sentencas: The chemical compatibility, electrochemical performance, morphology, and stability of the as-prepared composite electrodes were systematically investigated.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction

Sentencas: BSC infiltration at appropriate loadings was found to be beneficial for the reduction of the polarization resistance of the LNF electrode.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction

Sentencas: BSC overload resulted in an increase of the adsorption resistance, which deteriorated the ORR performance of the LNF cathode.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction

Sentencas: The calcination temperature of the BSC precursor was found to be a key parameter for the morphology as well as the electrochemical performance of the hybrid composite cathode.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction

Sentencas: For the cathode calcined at 900 degrees C, BSC nanoparticles diffused into the LNF scaffold through high temperature reaction sintering.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction

Sentencas: Moreover, the stability tests at 750 degrees C for 80 h in air revealed that the LNF cathode coated with a hybrid La(Ba, Sr) Ni(Fe, Co)O3-delta thin film through in-situ reaction sintering was far more stable than the counterpart infiltrated with nanoparticles.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction

Sentencas: This strategy via surface modification through an in-situ high temperature reaction may be extended to other electrode systems for SOFCs.
Titulo: Improved electrochemical activity and stability of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ cathodes achieved by an in-situ reaction
